21-28. Laertiaden :

Ulysses stole the Palladium and so sealed the fate of Troy.—Nestora: who kept the Greeks from abandoning the siege after Achilles' death. Od. 24, 51 ff.—Teucer: brother of Ajax and son ofTelemon; cf. 1, 7, 21 ff.—respicis: ‘as thou glancest backward in thy ssight.' The prophetie god sees the future so vividly that he conceives of the pursuit of Paris as already begun.
